body:
QR Code Link to This Post



Plow not included and not for sale. I will leave the plow on for $22000.00

Truck is coming off the road within a few days, so test drives will be limited to right around the corner from my house. No exceptions. 

It will be tough to find another 2500HD this clean with low miles like this! Try to find one that is not beat up also!

2004 Chevy Silverado 2500HD LS 4x4 crew cab long bed pickup. 36000 original miles. 6.0 liter gas engine, automatic. Black with gray cloth interior. Body is nice and the interior is nice. Never used commercially. Locking truck cap, bedliner, bed mat. BF Goodrich Radial All Terrain T/A KO tires with nice tread (load range E). 245/75R16. Trailer hitch receiver with 7 way round plug. (The truck never towed a trailer until 2012). Title is in my name. No liens!

Plow not included and not for sale (unless the price is right)! The truck had a plow on it for the past 3 years. Plow was a backup in case my smaller truck failed and I needed a way to clear my driveway. I never had to use it. It was a Meyer EZ Classic, so I didn't have to chop up the lower valance to mount the frame. Again, plow not included and not for sale!
. 
4x4 is electronic push button. Has a center console, AM/FM CD stereo (factory). 

All brake lines were changed over to stainless steel about 3 years ago. 

No lowball offers and no trades. That means, if you come over offering more than $1000 less than my asking price, you are wasting my time and your own time.

Serious inquiries only, please.

No daytime showings on weekdays. Weekend showings preferred. 

What it needs...

Headliner is starting to separate by the windshield. Sometimes, the check engine light will come on and blink, so there is probably a bad sensor somewhere. Heater control only works on settings four and five.

Everything under the hood was in good working order when I parked it about a year or so ago, no check engine light or nothing. Just went out today 3-5-2017 it started right up, pretty smokey and and now the check engine light is on, not sure if it's because it sat so long or not. Needs a grommet pin for the 4x4 to work. COPY AND PASTE THE LINK BELOW INTO A NEW BROWSER FOR OVER 80 PICTURES

s1382.photobucket.com/user/dstroeh/library/390143?sort=3&page=1

Maxxforce DT466 220hp Engine

Hello and thank you for taking the time to look at my auction. Please know that I am extremely detail oriented and when I recondition a truck I do it to the level as if I were going to keep it for myself. Needless to say I go much deeper into the detail on these trucks than anyone I have yet to come across. They are mechanically sound, clean as a pin and as close to brand new as I can get them within reason. 

We do not put a truck up for sale with any active codes.

This truck is a PRE-EMISSIONS 2007 International 4300 box truck with 316930 miles. This truck has a DT466 engine (220hp) and is in fantastic condition. No oil leaks and is as mechanically strong as they come. Behind the DT466 is the indestructible 5 speed Automatic Eaton Fuller transmission with overdrive followed by the Spicer rear end. This is one of the most reliable drive trains in the industry. 

This truck came out of a major National fleet with one of the best fleet maintenance records in the industry.

This truck can haul plenty of cargo, especially with the 25,999lb GVWR (NO CDL REQUIRED) and a 24' Truck Body and a Maxon 4400lb 78" X 62" liftgate. I drove this truck over 1100 miles to bring it back to North Carolina with absolutely no issues at all. It has a Whiting roll up door with an opening 91 1/2" wide x 89" tall and 102" wide x 97" tall overall dimension. Truck has an overall clearance of 12' 7". The box comes equipped with a translucent roof, 2 rows of E-Track and a side door.

Inside the cab, you'll find an AM/FM Radio, Air Conditioning, heat, Cruise control, 12v power outlet, an air ride driver's bucket seat and a passenger bench seat with a storage compartment underneath. One of the best features of this truck is the drive train. The Pre-Emissions DT466, the Eaton Fuller automatic transmission and the Spicer rear end are a bulletproof drive train combination. This combo has a proven track record over the years and is extremely reliable. Time has proven that if properly maintained it can go for 1 million miles without a rebuild. Another fantastic features of the DT466 is it's ability to be "in Frame Rebuilt" saving thousands if a rebuild is needed. It is becoming more and more difficult to find these Pre-emissions trucks with an automatic transmission. If you're searching for a great work truck in like new condition, you found it.

CONDITION REPORT
This truck is exceptionally clean. The entire frame from the cab back as well as the front suspension, have been sandblasted down to the bare metal primed and painted (3 coats). The handles, steps, differential, springs and mirrors have all been freshly painted. The engine has been steam cleaned and there are no oil leaks. The wheels, hubs and lug nuts have also been sandblasted and repainted. Inside I took the seats out cleaned and repainted the frames. The entire interior was steam cleaned including the back panel and headliner. All of the panels and dash shine and are not dull. The entire exterior of the box and cab (including the door jams) have been professionally repainted and looks fantastic. The interior of the box was steam cleaned as well as the oak floor. This truck is immaculate, clean as a pin. You can not appreciate it until you see it in person the pictures just don't do it justice. 

It is easy to tell that it has not been abused or overworked and obviously cared for properly. We send all of our trucks to the local dealer and have a health check run on them. They are gone through top to bottom and front to back. We spend an average of $3000 on the mechanical aspects alone when putting our trucks through the refurbishing process. We make all the necessary repairs to fix any and all issues that were identified. Cosmetically on this truck we replaced the headlights, gear shift cover, Dock Bumpers, and DOT Reflective Tape just to name afew items. There are absolutely no mechanical issues with this truck. It is a good solid runner ready to go to work. No squeaks/rattles at idle or cruising down the road. It is as quiet of a truck at as you will ever find. 

All of the interior features are functioning normally and there are no mechanical or drivability issues. It is sitting on 22.5" tires. The tire treads measure: front Left 10/32, Left rear outside 13/32, inside 13/32. Right front 11.5/32, right rear outside 12.7/32, inside 12.7/32. Please don't hesitate to email me with any questions you have and I will respond as soon as possible. I encourage communication and will gladly respond to all questions with as much information as I possibly can.
You will be hard pressed to find a truck in this condition for this price.

body:
QR Code Link to This Post



The last owner put on all of the aftermarket off-road parts but since I bought it I have put a ton of new parts on it as well (just trying to keep up with the routine maintenance and make sure that everything is in perfect working order). 

I would love to keep it but I have not been able to use it as much as I like due to my job (I am always out of state). I am selling this bad ass vehicle becuase I need to move to Idaho for work by early June.

If you're looking for an reliable off-road vehicle to have fun in this summer this is your ride. 

As you most likely guess it has the Straight Six 4.0L engine that made the 1990's Cherokee's one of the most reliable off-road vehicles ever made (Google it if you don't believe me lol). It gets about 15 mpg on average even with the lift. 

Exterior is not in perfect condition by any means (the fenders are cut for more articulation) but it looks good and with some aftermarket fender flares it would be mint. The only dent/ding is on the upper left side of the rear hatch (see pics above for reference).

Interior is in good condition but not perfect. It could use a detailing but there are no rips or tears in the seats and no large stains either. The only two things I did not like is that the roof liner has been taken off (I planned on having it replaced if I had kept it longer), and the inner plastic piece for the rear hatch is missing. Besides that the plastics/upholstery are in good condition no rips, tears, cracks etc. 

Tires are the 33" Goodyear Wrangler model and have about 60% life left. 

The whole time I have owned the Jeep I have only used Mobile 1 Oil and Premium Gas.

New Parts (I have added since I bought it):

-New Radio Deck (Pop-Out Touch Screen)
-New Front Component Speakers (Kenwood)
-New Rear Speakers (Planet Audio)
-New 12" Subwoofer (JBL)
-New Slim-Line 12" Sub Box
-New Wiring For Speaker System
-New Magnaflow Muffler
-New Magnaflow CAT

Hello and thank you for taking the time to look at my auction. Please know that I am extremely detail oriented and when I recondition a truck I do it to the level as if I were going to keep it for myself. Needless to say I go much deeper into the detail on these trucks than anyone I have yet to come across. They are mechanically sound, clean as a pin and as close to brand new as I can get them within reason. 

We do not put a truck up for sale with any active codes.

This truck is a PRE-EMISSIONS 2007 International 4300 box truck with 316930 miles. This truck has a DT466 engine (220hp) and is in fantastic condition. No oil leaks and is as mechanically strong as they come. Behind the DT466 is the indestructible 5 speed Automatic Eaton Fuller transmission with overdrive followed by the Spicer rear end. This is one of the most reliable drive trains in the industry. 

This truck came out of a major National fleet with one of the best fleet maintenance records in the industry.

This truck can haul plenty of cargo, especially with the 25,999lb GVWR (NO CDL REQUIRED) and a 24' Truck Body and a Maxon 4400lb 78" X 62" liftgate. I drove this truck over 1100 miles to bring it back to North Carolina with absolutely no issues at all. It has a Whiting roll up door with an opening 91 1/2" wide x 89" tall and 102" wide x 97" tall overall dimension. Truck has an overall clearance of 12' 7". The box comes equipped with a translucent roof, 2 rows of E-Track and a side door.

Inside the cab, you'll find an AM/FM Radio, Air Conditioning, heat, Cruise control, 12v power outlet, an air ride driver's bucket seat and a passenger bench seat with a storage compartment underneath. One of the best features of this truck is the drive train. The Pre-Emissions DT466, the Eaton Fuller automatic transmission and the Spicer rear end are a bulletproof drive train combination. This combo has a proven track record over the years and is extremely reliable. Time has proven that if properly maintained it can go for 1 million miles without a rebuild. Another fantastic features of the DT466 is it's ability to be "in Frame Rebuilt" saving thousands if a rebuild is needed. It is becoming more and more difficult to find these Pre-emissions trucks with an automatic transmission. If you're searching for a great work truck in like new condition, you found it.

CONDITION REPORT
This truck is exceptionally clean. The entire frame from the cab back as well as the front suspension, have been sandblasted down to the bare metal primed and painted (3 coats). The handles, steps, differential, springs and mirrors have all been freshly painted. The engine has been steam cleaned and there are no oil leaks. The wheels, hubs and lug nuts have also been sandblasted and repainted. Inside I took the seats out cleaned and repainted the frames. The entire interior was steam cleaned including the back panel and headliner. All of the panels and dash shine and are not dull. The entire exterior of the box and cab (including the door jams) have been professionally repainted and looks fantastic. The interior of the box was steam cleaned as well as the oak floor. This truck is immaculate, clean as a pin. You can not appreciate it until you see it in person the pictures just don't do it justice. 

It is easy to tell that it has not been abused or overworked and obviously cared for properly. We send all of our trucks to the local dealer and have a health check run on them. They are gone through top to bottom and front to back. We spend an average of $3000 on the mechanical aspects alone when putting our trucks through the refurbishing process. We make all the necessary repairs to fix any and all issues that were identified. Cosmetically on this truck we replaced the headlights, gear shift cover, Dock Bumpers, and DOT Reflective Tape just to name afew items. There are absolutely no mechanical issues with this truck. It is a good solid runner ready to go to work. No squeaks/rattles at idle or cruising down the road. It is as quiet of a truck at as you will ever find. 

All of the interior features are functioning normally and there are no mechanical or drivability issues. It is sitting on 22.5" tires. The tire treads measure: front Left 10/32, Left rear outside 13/32, inside 13/32. Right front 11.5/32, right rear outside 12.7/32, inside 12.7/32. Please don't hesitate to email me with any questions you have and I will respond as soon as possible. I encourage communication and will gladly respond to all questions with as much information as I possibly can.
You will be hard pressed to find a truck in this condition for this price.

In the one Picture of the flooring carpet.. the picture for what ever reason makes it look worse then it is. We had a center plastic carrier for drinks and such there. I haven't tried to carpet clean it.. but I am sure it would come out. It really isn't noticeable in person.

We purchased this Truck December 2008 and it only had 49,500 miles on it. It now has now at this time 121,684. Miles might go up just a tad when people test drive it. Won't be anything major.

This has always been a very dependable truck. Still is. We simply decided to up grade to an extend cab so we do not need this one any longer. For the past 4 years this has not been a daily driver.
We have mainly only been using it to haul things every once in a great while.. to go fishing or once in a while a trip to visit family in Richmond.

Tires are still like brand new! We have always kept oil maintenance on this truck, although I believe an oil change is due again. Not planing on getting that done because as of right now no longer driving it. Battery if I remember properly was purchased within this past year. No major work has ever been needed. Did have Intake gasket replaced last summer. For the year of this truck it is in pretty good shape and very dependable.

It does have the engine light on, which we had checked out. It is for an emission error.. which we simply was not concerned with and haven't for the past 2 years. Has not effected this truck at all. Does have 2 really small dents on the top edge of the truck bed. Also some paint bubbling just above the wheel wells, which seems to be a typical issue with these trucks. We wouldn't consider selling this if we hadn't gotten another truck. Just tired of a single cab and that is the only reason. If you decide you really want the truck and would like to confirm the check engine light we have an auto zone not far from us where we can have it hooked up for you. 
This has NEVER been in any accidents! Top head liner and drivers seat have been repaired.

Current milage is around 158K.  I drive it nearly every day, so that will slowly rise.

Not everything is perfect about this truck.  It had some scratches and a small dent on the drivers side when I bought it.  It also has some rusting at the rear cab posts on both driver and passenger sides.  I did some research and found this to be a common issue with Ford Cabs with sun-roofs in particular.  Driver's seat has a tear at the edge when you get into the vehicle.  Pervious owner put a seat cover over it.  I always intended to get better ones.  Procrastination.  There are some other cosmetic blemishes, but it still looks awesome in spite of these.

Just had breaks completely redone front and back.  The break light remains on in the dash in spite of this.  The break folks tell me it is most likely the sensor for the emergency break lever.  Put new tires on the back recently after getting something punched through the side wall.  Front tires are quite new with at least 80% tread remaining.

I am pricing this to sell.  KBB puts this truck at $8188.  $1500 discount for cometic issues!  So selling at a loss for $6688 (FIRM)

My requirements for sale:  CASH.  Cash only.  No other payment method accepted.  I will not deal with you using PayPal or eBay.  If you ask I will just ignore you.  Scammers wasting my time can take a hike.  Sale in Kentucky require a Notary , so we would need to conduct business face to face and during business hours.

body:
QR Code Link to This Post



Nice rust-free Virginia truck with original paint except for hood. Bed is original paint with no dents or rust. 
These are hard to find so well kept. You will enjoy this truck as is or it could easily be taken to show truck stage. 
Window sticker and owner's manual included as well as receipts for work below. Everything works, even the cassette deck! I drive it every day. Selling to focus on an old truck restoration.

Nice Factory Options: Silver with light gray interior, Silverado Trim, 5.7L Engine, 4L60E auto/overdrive transmission, A/C, tach. Interior is superb with no rips in seat or cracks on dash

Drivetrain is very strong with no issues (no knocks, rattles or smoke). 4WD works fine.

Work performed in 2016. Cost includes parts and labor:
All new A/C system $1000
New aluminum wheels w/ BFG LT265/75R16 KO2 Tires	$1300 (less than 4000 miles)
New Magnaflow engine back cat assembly and 3in Gibson exhaust	$1300	(all stainless)
Rough Country leveling kit and Z71 shocks (Bilstien) $500
All new brakes: rotors, drums, wheel cylinders, pads and shoes	$650
Tune with new wires/rotor/cap/plugs	$250
New fuel injectors (TBI)	$250
AC Delco OEM battery cables (10 times better than parts store)	$150
Misc: engine sensors, thermostat, EGR, bed mat, dash cover, other	$400

There is lower bed side dent just behind passenger side cab. Service engine light comes on occasionally during colder weather. This is "code 32" EGR, all components replaced within last year. Nothing more you can do to prevent it, but does not affect the engine performance at all. Oil just changed.

title: 2001 F-350 superduty 7.3 Turbo Diesel

body:
QR Code Link to This Post


A lot of time and energy( and money) as gone into building a rust free and mechanically sound rig.
Has a fresh inspection sticker and for those of you who understand what it takes to get a vehicle inspected in Vermont now will know what kind of mechanical shape it needs to be in.
140,000 on a tight 22RE 4cylinder. 
The oil stays up on the stick, hasn't 
moved at all. No leaks and no burning. Tons of power.
Whole brake system gone through including lines. New shoes, cylinders, rotors, pads, calipers, e-brake cables. You just touch the brakes and you stop fast.
New ball joints, all four(quality ones), tie rod ends, idle arm.
New shocks all around and steering stabilizer.
New fuel pump and sending unit.
New tires and rims. Dunlop Rovers.
I am including a nearly new set of 31" General Grabbers and aluminum rims.
Also includes a fiberglass cap(a little rough but looks good and works well)
4wd works and shifts well.
Front Hubs lock in and out freely.
Nice comfy bucket seats.
Freshly oil under coated.
New exhaust, manifold back, including cat and O2 sensor.
Nice Kenwood stereo w/ CD player.
This truck has lots and lots of trouble free miles ahead of it.
This was put together as a dream truck but unfortunately life throws curves so dreams have to be sold.
Someone else will benefit from all that went into this beauty.
You would be hard pressed to find a cleaner truck in Florida or out west.
Email or texts are welcome as well as phone calls.
No trades, just cash. Thanks

cylinders: 8 cylinders
drive: 4wd
fuel: gas
title status: clean
transmission: automatic
type: pickup
I have had this truck for 7 years. I have fixed all mechanical issues that the truck had when I got it. It runs and drives great. I had intentions of fixing the body and getting it painted, but I want a motorcycle and have decided to sell the truck. With that being said, it is not a show truck. It is a good dependable truck that you can make your own. The truck has been kept out of the weather and taken care of. It has not been abused. I have listed the repairs/upgrades that I have done below: 
-replaced the steering box
-braced frame at steering box
-installed 4 inch rough country lift
-new shocks and steering stablilizer
-drop pitman arm
-new sway bar bushings
-new cab bushings
-new master cylinder and brakes
-extended braided brake lines
-transmission serviced
-transfer case rebuilt
-new hubs
-lock in lock out hub kit installed with superwinch hubs
-new radiator
-new alternator
-all fluids changed
-I'm sure I missed something, but that is the main things I have done.

All of that has been done in the last 2000 miles or so by a mechanic. The truck has a 350 with a turbo 350 transmission. 10 bolt gm front end and 12 bolt rear. 

Don't let this trucks appearance scare you away, if you are looking for a solid old model truck, let me know and we can meet up so you can look it over.

body:
QR Code Link to This Post



- 4" lift
- 35" new tires
- Power steering
- Brakes have recently been converted from drum to modern disc
- New steering rod kit
- New top with family style roll bars
- Corbeau front and rear seats
- Strong, re-built running V-8, 302 cu. in. | Starts immediately, runs great
- Sony Radio included, installed in security center console (not connected)
- Main Fuel Tank = 12.7 gallons
- "Wild Horses Logo" on sides of Bronco can easily be removed by buyer.

Transparent list of required or recommended necessary improvements if I were to keep the vehicle:

- Vehicle drives "loose" which is very common for these vehicles, but not so much for someone who has experience driving early model vehicles - however it is noticeable for someone who has only driven late model vehicles and does take some adjusting until you are comfortable with the feel of the vehicle. Rebuilding steering box, approximately $200.00 or buying a new one, approximately $500.00 may help improve the "loose" steering.
- Speedometer will fluctuate greatly once above 60 mph.
- Gas gauge will stay on F considerably longer than it should. As a general rule of thumb, when the gas gauge shows 1/2 full, I fill up. 
- Odometer is not working. Vehicle was lightly driven by previous owner after engine rebuild and stays parked in my garage 5 or 6 days out of the week.
- Hood grommets needs to be replaced.
- Lift support for hood is recommended.
- Replacement battery tray is needed.
- No fan guard on radiator. Highly recommended that one be installed by new owner to prevent an unnecessary accident if looking under the hood while engine is on.
- Auxiliary tank, i.e. 2nd tank is not connected.
- Rear brake lights have a loose connection. 
- Center console needs to be bolted into floorboard.
- "Marine" type speakers to connect to Sony Radio are recommended.

Ford only created 21,894 Broncos for this model year. This Bronco is garage kept at my house. A similar 1973 Ford Bronco (no back seat) was sold last weekend (4/8/2017) in Houston at the Meachum Auction for $24,000, plus the buyer had to pay a $2,400 auction fee.

- Clean title in hand. 
- Serious and qualified inquiries only. 
- Not interested in trades or shipping vehicle sight unseen. 
- Appointment for local test drive will be scheduled at a safe location for you and me. 
- Buyer is buying a "classic" vehicle. 
- Bronco is being sold "as is," and no warranty is implied.

All that Powered by a 6.0 Vortec engine: The 6.0L is powerful, but delivers exceptional refinement to go with great strength. Quiet features built into the engine are complemented by an improved engine cradle and mounting system. These help reduce vibrations transmitted through the chassis and into the passenger compartment.

http://gmauthority.com/blog/gm/gm-engines/l96/#ixzz4fqMjhzD2

body:
QR Code Link to This Post



COPY AND PASTE THE LINK BELOW INTO A NEW BROWSER FOR OVER 80 PICTURES

s1382.photobucket.com/user/dstroeh/library/390143?sort=3&page=1


OVERVIEW

VIN Number 1HTMPAFM37H390XXX

Features/Options:

Air Brakes
Dual Fuel Tanks

24' Box
102" Box
Translucent Roof
Vented Box
Side Door

Air Conditioning
AM/FM Radio
Spring Suspension
25,999 lb GVWR
254" Wheelbase
Maxxforce DT466 220hp Engine

Hello and thank you for taking the time to look at my auction. Please know that I am extremely detail oriented and when I recondition a truck I do it to the level as if I were going to keep it for myself. Needless to say I go much deeper into the detail on these trucks than anyone I have yet to come across. They are mechanically sound, clean as a pin and as close to brand new as I can get them within reason. 

We do not put a truck up for sale with any active codes.

This truck is a PRE-EMISSIONS 2007 International 4300 box truck with 316930 miles. This truck has a DT466 engine (220hp) and is in fantastic condition. No oil leaks and is as mechanically strong as they come. Behind the DT466 is the indestructible 5 speed Automatic Eaton Fuller transmission with overdrive followed by the Spicer rear end. This is one of the most reliable drive trains in the industry. 

This truck came out of a major National fleet with one of the best fleet maintenance records in the industry.

This truck can haul plenty of cargo, especially with the 25,999lb GVWR (NO CDL REQUIRED) and a 24' Truck Body and a Maxon 4400lb 78" X 62" liftgate. I drove this truck over 1100 miles to bring it back to North Carolina with absolutely no issues at all. It has a Whiting roll up door with an opening 91 1/2" wide x 89" tall and 102" wide x 97" tall overall dimension. Truck has an overall clearance of 12' 7". The box comes equipped with a translucent roof, 2 rows of E-Track and a side door.

Inside the cab, you'll find an AM/FM Radio, Air Conditioning, heat, Cruise control, 12v power outlet, an air ride driver's bucket seat and a passenger bench seat with a storage compartment underneath. One of the best features of this truck is the drive train. The Pre-Emissions DT466, the Eaton Fuller automatic transmission and the Spicer rear end are a bulletproof drive train combination. This combo has a proven track record over the years and is extremely reliable. Time has proven that if properly maintained it can go for 1 million miles without a rebuild. Another fantastic features of the DT466 is it's ability to be "in Frame Rebuilt" saving thousands if a rebuild is needed. It is becoming more and more difficult to find these Pre-emissions trucks with an automatic transmission. If you're searching for a great work truck in like new condition, you found it.

CONDITION REPORT
This truck is exceptionally clean. The entire frame from the cab back as well as the front suspension, have been sandblasted down to the bare metal primed and painted (3 coats). The handles, steps, differential, springs and mirrors have all been freshly painted. The engine has been steam cleaned and there are no oil leaks. The wheels, hubs and lug nuts have also been sandblasted and repainted. Inside I took the seats out cleaned and repainted the frames. The entire interior was steam cleaned including the back panel and headliner. All of the panels and dash shine and are not dull. The entire exterior of the box and cab (including the door jams) have been professionally repainted and looks fantastic. The interior of the box was steam cleaned as well as the oak floor. This truck is immaculate, clean as a pin. You can not appreciate it until you see it in person the pictures just don't do it justice. 

It is easy to tell that it has not been abused or overworked and obviously cared for properly. We send all of our trucks to the local dealer and have a health check run on them. They are gone through top to bottom and front to back. We spend an average of $3000 on the mechanical aspects alone when putting our trucks through the refurbishing process. We make all the necessary repairs to fix any and all issues that were identified. Cosmetically on this truck we replaced the headlights, gear shift cover, Dock Bumpers, and DOT Reflective Tape just to name afew items. There are absolutely no mechanical issues with this truck. It is a good solid runner ready to go to work. No squeaks/rattles at idle or cruising down the road. It is as quiet of a truck at as you will ever find. 

All of the interior features are functioning normally and there are no mechanical or drivability issues. It is sitting on 22.5" tires. The tire treads measure: front Left 10/32, Left rear outside 13/32, inside 13/32. Right front 11.5/32, right rear outside 12.7/32, inside 12.7/32. Please don't hesitate to email me with any questions you have and I will respond as soon as possible. I encourage communication and will gladly respond to all questions with as much information as I possibly can.
You will be hard pressed to find a truck in this condition for this price.

Truck runs fine.  I bought it with a broken clutch setup due to well known Toyota truck issue with cracked clutch pedal assembly/cracked firewall.  Repaired firewall/clutch pedal assembly, and also patched the frame (shown in pix).  Rest of frame looks pretty good.

Someone did good job building bed for this rig, and the truck needs some TLC but is ready to drive/trail run.  Interior carpet was coated in rhinoliner, or some poly-paint making it pretty waterproof.

Rust under doors on cab is pretty rough, but generally truck is a good starting spot to build a pretty tough on or off road rig.

Bed is all steel including deck, and tire mount is on swingaway.  Lights/wipers/etc work fine.  Tires are in good shape.  Brakes are a little soft.     Snorkel is not currently hooked up.

Cash only! NO TRADES! (like really, absolutely NO TRADES)!

body:
QR Code Link to This Post



The interior is ok, no rips or holes in the seats or carpet.  The radio is a JVC AM/FM/CD with USB, Bluetooth and a Backup Camera.

Yes, it has 177k miles, but it still runs great.  I've always run Amzoil synthetics in the motor, transmission and power steering.  The 496 c.i. (8.1L) with the Allison transmission is the best,  biggest most powerful gas combination ever put in a passenger pickup.  

The truck comes with a Snug-Top canopy, running boards, 5th wheel hitch,  gooseneck adapter,  brake controller, Extendable Mirrors and is ready to pull just about anything you want to throw at it.   The tires were replaced this past fall with Toyo Open Country's. 

If you're interested in replacing the fender, the whole side is plastic,  removable and under $300.  This is a good truck.  If you're looking for a $4000 truck, go look at a $4000 truck.  This truck is far from perfect,  but I'm selling it for what I think it's worth for the condition.  

I'm not interested in trades, just want good ol' fashioned cash.

body:
QR Code Link to This Post



Very Clean and reliable truck! Front bumper is rusting from stone chips that never got fixed then the Michigan winters taking its toll on the bare steel. Rest of the truck has very little to no rust.

Aftermarket addons: 
K&N injection intake kit, plus spare filter. 
Flowmaster stainless steel catback exhaust system
Firestone ride rite pneumatic helper springs with interior gauge(Manual fill)
Manual extending tow mirrors (power, heated & blinkers)
Linex performance bed liner
LED third break light
LED reverse bulbs
Tonneau cover
Tinted front windows (matching factory rear tint)
Custom painted wheels to match bottom two tone of truck
Performance breaks for towing, drilled and slotted rotors on all corners (Powerstop Brand)
Trailer break controller 
Factory Premium sound with factory subwoofer
Comes with a lifetime supply of Bosch oil filters because I bought a case at one point
Had the spark plugs changed last year (cuz that engine is a pain to do that to) same visit they rebuilt the rear axle because it lost a bearing in the carrier. A month later I had a new transmission installed because I lost my reverse gear and it made more sense to replace than to have rebuilt. Transmission is still under warranty.
Drivers seat upholstery has been replaced with a new oem cover.

Tread depth on the tires isn't the best, would recommend new tires within the next year or so. They could probably get another year out of them if needed.

I don't really want to sell it but I upgraded to a diesel and my wife won't let me keep both. I am the second owner. 

Can be seen on the Corner of Michigan Ave (M89) and Augusta Dr. in front of West Point Corner Storage.

Asking $9000 obo

body:
QR Code Link to This Post


 .....The fuel injected 460 under the hood starts easy and runs strong , strong backed by a solid 5 speed manual transmission that shifts smooth and easy.  Everything works as it should and she's pretty darn clean inside and out. It does need the passenger side mirror replaced , it is missing the center knob on the climate control cluster and the dome light lense , all of which are easy and cheap to replace . The hood latch is stodgy from salt fly and it did not come from the factory with A/C but the heater does work great and the windows roll down easy plus it's got wing windows for extra a/c . Tires are are roadworthy but not real meaty.  Body is clean and paint is solid but the clear coat is peeling in places. Did I mention it has a great seat? 
.....The service bed is a 1994 Pelsue with tons of storage and good solid latching turn style locks ( not the junk slam doors that won't latch). It has dual electric air compressors , forced air blower with heat , 3 - 120 vac tgi outlets and 2 - 30 amp 240 vac outlets. Supply for all this comes from a well maintained Kohler 10,000 watt generator powered by a smooth running , strong 4 cylinder gas Ford engine. Parts of the service body do show rust from road salt  but by and large she's a great truck with loads of job life ahead of her. 
...... I prefer to sell her whole but I'm willing to split it up for serious buyer. I'm asking $3500 obo for the whole kit and kaboodle but I might consider $2500 for the truck and service bed minus generator , power points and air or $2000 for the Cab and Chassis alone. Please keep in mind I will have to separate these units if you only want one piece or the other which isn't a simple job so I would require a substantial down payment before I start into it. Might consider some trading on solid small tractor with loader , solid 4 wheeler , stock trailer , flatbed trailer , enclosed trailer , 4x4 little truck (NOT Chevrolet) , or ?. If you're interested you can respond via craigslist or call /text me at four06-3one4-885four. Hopefully , I listed it all but feel free to ask questions .Thanks for viewing and look forward to hearing from you.

title: 91 Ford Ranger ext cab

body:
QR Code Link to This Post



Free and clear title- newly assigned state vin number, original vin tag was gone.

3 Stick Trannie/transfer - T-90 / Dana 18 as far as I can tell.

Early 90's 305 SBC from a Camaro, according to the casting numbers, besides the cheap walmart battery, which is mounted in the rear, the engine starts and purrs great. I rewired the majority of the Jeep with Weatherpack connectors. Part of the reason I am getting rid of it is because, I am more of a blue oval fan, which would have been much more gentle on the firewall (distributor would have been in the CORRECT spot!)  and if I did keep it, I would surely destroy my perfect driving record, well at least for the last decade. This Jeep has a s@#$load of power and should not be taken likely!!!

All new brake pads and rebuilt slave cylinders, new oem style gauge cluster, new speedo- IT HAS LESS THAN 20 MILES! WHAT A DEAL! Haha, unknown actual miles. Could use some bigger tires, considering the power it has and it tops out around 55-60 with the motor wound up pretty tight. New under seat fuel tank, filters and lines. Transfer case was drained and refilled, new output seal installed, park brake drum was serviced at the time, just needs cable and handle. All boxes topped off.
I separated the trans from the motor and installed a new throw out bearing last fall, also to see if whoever did the swap used a good adapter kit, besides the trashed throw out bearing everything looked good.

Replaced rear tail/brake lights with led, added led turns in the front, micro led backup lamps, new turn signal switch (universal style) mounted on steering column.

New glass and rubber in windshield, new visors, and rear view mirror.

Previous owner removed the original seats, actually just cut the backs off and welded another set to the bases, with a little material and bending someone might be able to rebuild the backs and put a more original seat back in it. There is no rear seat.
Small box of extra parts also...

The whole body is original steel, except for the aftermarket fiberglass hood, it had some rust/bare spots when I got it, so instead of letting the rust get worse, I did a quick scuff and spray on it to protect it more, it is by no means a professional paint job, and definitely not the best I have ever done! Punisher sticker on the hood just seemed fitting for that little brute... Doesn't look bad from a distance, or in pictures, but would have to see the true condition up close.

As I said earlier it has a newly assigned state vin, and a brand new title ready to go, It is titled and vin tagged as a CJ-3A 1949, I also have a Willys overland reprod vin tag to cover the ugly state assigned tag, that was the best I could identify it due to the windshield and the radiator mount mostly. I had this jeep advertised a year ago, without a title or vin number, and stated that I would ask more if I went through the whole 370+ days process with the state for a new vin, well at least that's done and over with.

I am asking 5500.00 OBO for the Jeep, but I will consider partial  trade for bike for my daughter, preferably around a 250 size 4 stroke, other than that not really looking for anything else. Not wanting super bad to get rid of it, but I would like to do another one with a small block Ford instead.

Last summer when I had this jeep parked out front, several people wanted and would have bought it if there had been a title for it, well besides a notary, this is a brand new title ready to go.

Map should show location if you just want to do a drive by, I will probably have it parked out by the highway during the day, as long as its not raining.

Anyways, the wife says I ramble on too much, so there's the skinny on the Willy!

Have a great day, looks like the sun is going to finally shine today!
title: 1949 Willys Overland Jeep CJ-3A SBC

According to the service garage they recommend that all the breaks lines be replaced.  This truck does run, but needs a new battery.   The truck does not leak or burn oil, when I purchased the previous owner said that he rebuilt the engine around 200K, have no proof, but it did run well when I drove it last summer.

If anyone is interested send me an offer (more info below)?

Truck has (4) nice tires with steel wheels and a full size spare, also has the jack assembly and bedliner. Interior is in decent shape with a new radio installed with CD player (last year). All lights, wipers, horn, radio w/ CD player and heater work.  All glass is good, not broken or cracked.

Passenger outside mirror missing and  the passenger door wont stay closed, I used a cable to keep it shut.

body:
QR Code Link to This Post



If anyone has a decent square body S10, that's what I'm wanting to trade for.  Thanks.

HO 4.3L with a 5 speed. 
Power windows, locks, mirrors, cruise, tilt, and AC that will freeze your nuts off. 

Motor was rebuilt 45k miles ago.  Has new distributor, cap, plugs, wires, water pump, battery, and starter.  It also has an all aluminum radiator and 175 degree thermostat.  Absolutely zero cooling issues.  Throttle body has been bored out.

New tires and brakes with drilled and slotted rotors.

Transmission has new clutch, slave cylinder, and pressure plate.  

Interior is clean.  New dash, headliner, visors, carpet, and cavalier seats.  Tinted windows and sliding rear window as well. 

She has the ZQ8 suspension (lowered and bigger sway bars) but has been lowered additionally with DJM spindles and shackles.  I have original spindles. 

Nice pioneer stereo with the Bluetooth mic already run.  LEDs all around and in the interior.

THE BAD...  

She's a Mona Lisa.  A previous owner was a painter.  So the bed has spills of paint all over the inside of it.  But beds are cheap and was planning on just replacing it.  Some dents here and there.  It's my daily driver so as long as it was mechanically sound and the interior was comfortable, I was happy.

And it pulls a little to the right.  Probably needs an alignment.

Message me via text preferably.  This is my daily driver so miles will go up.

body:
QR Code Link to This Post



COPY AND PASTE THE LINK BELOW INTO A NEW BROWSER FOR OVER 80 PICTURES

s1382.photobucket.com/user/dstroeh/library/390143?sort=3&page=1


OVERVIEW

VIN Number 1HTMPAFM37H390XXX

Features/Options:

Air Brakes
Dual Fuel Tanks
Air Ride Drivers Seat
24' Box
102" Box
Translucent Roof
Vented Box
Side Door
2 Rows of E-Track
Maxon 400lb Self Leveling Liftgate 78" X 62"
Air Conditioning
AM/FM Radio
Spring Suspension
25,999 lb GVWR
254" Wheelbase
Maxxforce DT466 220hp Engine

Hello and thank you for taking the time to look at my auction. Please know that I am extremely detail oriented and when I recondition a truck I do it to the level as if I were going to keep it for myself. Needless to say I go much deeper into the detail on these trucks than anyone I have yet to come across. They are mechanically sound, clean as a pin and as close to brand new as I can get them within reason. 

We do not put a truck up for sale with any active codes.

This truck is a PRE-EMISSIONS 2007 International 4300 box truck with 316930 miles. This truck has a DT466 engine (220hp) and is in fantastic condition. No oil leaks and is as mechanically strong as they come. Behind the DT466 is the indestructible 5 speed Automatic Eaton Fuller transmission with overdrive followed by the Spicer rear end. This is one of the most reliable drive trains in the industry. 

This truck came out of a major National fleet with one of the best fleet maintenance records in the industry.

This truck can haul plenty of cargo, especially with the 25,999lb GVWR (NO CDL REQUIRED) and a 24' Truck Body and a Maxon 4400lb 78" X 62" liftgate. I drove this truck over 1100 miles to bring it back to North Carolina with absolutely no issues at all. It has a Whiting roll up door with an opening 91 1/2" wide x 89" tall and 102" wide x 97" tall overall dimension. Truck has an overall clearance of 12' 7". The box comes equipped with a translucent roof, 2 rows of E-Track and a side door.

Inside the cab, you'll find an AM/FM Radio, Air Conditioning, heat, Cruise control, 12v power outlet, an air ride driver's bucket seat and a passenger bench seat with a storage compartment underneath. One of the best features of this truck is the drive train. The Pre-Emissions DT466, the Eaton Fuller automatic transmission and the Spicer rear end are a bulletproof drive train combination. This combo has a proven track record over the years and is extremely reliable. Time has proven that if properly maintained it can go for 1 million miles without a rebuild. Another fantastic features of the DT466 is it's ability to be "in Frame Rebuilt" saving thousands if a rebuild is needed. It is becoming more and more difficult to find these Pre-emissions trucks with an automatic transmission. If you're searching for a great work truck in like new condition, you found it.

CONDITION REPORT
This truck is exceptionally clean. The entire frame from the cab back as well as the front suspension, have been sandblasted down to the bare metal primed and painted (3 coats). The handles, steps, differential, springs and mirrors have all been freshly painted. The engine has been steam cleaned and there are no oil leaks. The wheels, hubs and lug nuts have also been sandblasted and repainted. Inside I took the seats out cleaned and repainted the frames. The entire interior was steam cleaned including the back panel and headliner. All of the panels and dash shine and are not dull. The entire exterior of the box and cab (including the door jams) have been professionally repainted and looks fantastic. The interior of the box was steam cleaned as well as the oak floor. This truck is immaculate, clean as a pin. You can not appreciate it until you see it in person the pictures just don't do it justice. 

It is easy to tell that it has not been abused or overworked and obviously cared for properly. We send all of our trucks to the local dealer and have a health check run on them. They are gone through top to bottom and front to back. We spend an average of $3000 on the mechanical aspects alone when putting our trucks through the refurbishing process. We make all the necessary repairs to fix any and all issues that were identified. Cosmetically on this truck we replaced the headlights, gear shift cover, Dock Bumpers, and DOT Reflective Tape just to name afew items. There are absolutely no mechanical issues with this truck. It is a good solid runner ready to go to work. No squeaks/rattles at idle or cruising down the road. It is as quiet of a truck at as you will ever find. 

All of the interior features are functioning normally and there are no mechanical or drivability issues. It is sitting on 22.5" tires. The tire treads measure: front Left 10/32, Left rear outside 13/32, inside 13/32. Right front 11.5/32, right rear outside 12.7/32, inside 12.7/32. Please don't hesitate to email me with any questions you have and I will respond as soon as possible. I encourage communication and will gladly respond to all questions with as much information as I possibly can.
You will be hard pressed to find a truck in this condition for this price.

title: 1984 Dodge D150

body:
QR Code Link to This Post




Please read All of the ad

Just added the mileage (thanks to a caller) the truck has 92,824 orginal  miles but will go up as I drive it.

1987 Ford F-250 EXT cab, 8' body. 7500 GVW  
(so it really is a single wheel 1 ton) 

It has three hitches, a frame mounted 2" receiver, goose neck and a 5th wheel. 
it will haul your trailer, horse trailer or camper.
Great truck for your farm or ranch.

Everything is heavy duty on this truck, you can pull or tow just about anything and even push snow, 
it has an 8' Fisher speedcast single lever control quick switch snowplow with a brand new cutting edge.
the controls and pump are mounted under the hood so there is no freezing problems in winter.

This is the first time this truck ever had a plow on it and I only plowed once in January (see photo) as we did not get much snow (3") in Southeast Iowa this year.

Looks black but is really a deep blue, pretty when cleaned up.

Last December (2016) I put on a new master cylinder, new brake lines, new starter solenoid, new center bearing, new heater motor  and a new fuel pump.
Tires are fair, still dig good in the snow and mud.


460 (7.5 cid) has a Holly (I think a 750 double pumper) carburetor, starts great and runs good, has a strong C-6 transmission with a shift kit, ideal for long distance towing, 

the 4x4 works great, has manual lockouts, not a lot of rust for the year,  still a strong and usable work truck.

The truck is set up for A/C but I took the pump off in order to mount the plow pump also had to remove the front bumper. 
(I still have the a/c pump and front bumper)

It has a blue bench seat in it now but I still have the original deep red buckets and console, these will all go with the truck.

Has tilt wheel cruse and tinted windows, there is a CD player radio, was told it works but the power wire is not hooked up, I do not listen to radio so I have not fixed it.

comes with all the "goodies" toolbox, diamond plate rails, razorback, cb antenna, air gate, sliding rear window,
(the air horns are for looks only not hooked up) and has a backup beeper. also have a set of aluminum diamond plate running boards to go with it,

I am including a long set of professional jumper cables (like wreckers have) 
the truck side is hooked to the battery and the plug is mounted to the plow gear so you can boost someone and never open your hood.
Has a good battery in it.


Has a few minor issues, front truck blinkers are not hooked up, 
(plow blinkers work) 

The rear gas tank leaks (like most Fords), there is a small crack in the windshield on the lower drivers side but does not affect vision. 
The lift piston does leak a little, needs  new seals (currently I have a travel chain attached so it will not drop while driving)
the power windows work from time to time, (sometimes they will work and sometimes they do not)
I believe that the switches just need to be cleaned. 

It is not a new truck but it is a tough one and loaded with power. 
Tires are fair and will need two new mufflers  
(kinda loud rumble now)

Reason for selling, don't need such a heavy duty truck anymore.

Cash is king, selling complete, (will not separate) asking $3,200 or obro cash offer but am not giving it away, 
remember, it is a good money maker for next winter and it is a lot of truck for the money.

Please no spam, if the ad is still up, it is still available, if you want it, 

please call. text is okay if you are serious but prefer calls.

Will not hold (unless you are coming to buy it that day) no paypal, no checks, will not sell on time and will not ship.
do not need help selling it.

If you are serious and want the truck, we can do business.

Thank you for looking

- 4 wheel drive with high and low range

body:
QR Code Link to This Post


Hello,




Up for sale is a 2000 Ford F-250 plow truck. It was purchased used 2 seasons ago and barely used due to the light winters. It is in decent shape with the typical ford rust. It was origianally used exclusively as a plow for Hilbert college. 
The good:
I was told when I bought it the transmission was completely rebuilt though I don't have paperwork to show it. 74,000 original miles and runs just fine. No check engine light. Upgraded suspension. Brand new manifolds and exhaust (pipes cat and muffler) all the way back. Was very expensive to have done.  New rear calipers, pads and rotors. Also an upgraded stereo with Bluetooth audio streaming and hands free calling. The plow works great and the pump was rebuilt last season.  All new hoses and connectors and other new parts.  It has the 5.4 V8 engine.  Strong runner and fires right up.  The bed is in good shape.  The pic has some wood laying in it because I was transporting drywall and needed a flat surface since there are tiedown hooks.  Brand new tailgate painted to match.  Tow package.  Lifted with leaf springs.  Auto lock 4x4.  Engages and disengages just fine.  

The bad:
The plow blade has rust and small holes but is covered with vinyl. It's in good shape but is 17 years old so there is rust like all fords of this time frame. There are scratches and dents as pictured. The AC has been removed.  Needs a front passenger tire or belt repaired.  It's bulged a bit and wobbles.  Holds air though.    





The only reason I am selling it is because I used to work in orchard park but needed an occasional utility truck. I figured it would be more economical to drive my efficient car to work and use the truck when needed. I got a new closer job so now I am going to sell both vehicles and get a newer smaller truck. 

Local pickup only.  I am located in Tonawanda/Buffalo NY.  Feel free to request to look at it.  I'm happy to show it just about any time.  Seven one 6 2 five four 77 seven one.
Thanks!

body:
QR Code Link to This Post



The paint is in good condition. The inside and top of tailgate and the bed rails are rhino-lined as well as the lower 1/8 of the body to protect the paint from rock chips. Truck has a receiver hitch and plug in for towing, keyless start and locks, tilt steering, great AC and heater, power windows, locks, breaks, steering, and also power heated mirrors. Pioneer CD player with iPod and mp3 player compatibility, also has phone connection capability, works and sounds good. Dual front air bags. Has a matching dash cover, custom fit Husky liner floor mats in the front and back. Interior and seats are in very good condition, I have always kept seat covers on the front seats. 

Windshield and all glass in good shape, one small chip low in the windshield has been repaired. Has block heater plug-in. Comes with a good spare tire mounted on matching aluminum rim. A few, maybe 2 or 3, very small door dings, but no paint damage. The only thing that doesn't work is the horn and I've never tried to fix it because it never bugged me. I'm only selling to buy a suburban for my growing family.

Asking $7200.00 or best cash offer.

I will not respond to any e-mails or texts. Only direct phone calls and NO dealers, and no I don't need or want help selling this truck. Please CALL four 0 six 4 five 9 five 0 two 2.  I do not reply to texts...I am old enough to have an aversion to texting and old enough to take excellent care of my vehicles!!!

The emerald green metallic paint looks great besides a few scratches, there's a few door dings, and a small dent on the passenger side (see pictures). One things it could use is a new hood, which will run about $100-$150. Of course that hood would need paint like the majority of older jeeps. Garage kept since the day I bought it, it has been lightly used and taken on a dirt road only three times. I have put a lot of time, effort, and money into this Jeep. The truck is completely stock except for a new HO after market fuel pump.
This truck runs and drives excellent. 
It has a 172000 on it and only 120000 on the transmission and transfer case.
Its has remote start system, blue tooth stereo, keyless entry, power windows, mirrors, locks. 
Power drivers seat and adjustable pedals.
Its got a nice $1500 Ranch hand bumper spray in bed liner and a tow package and a B&W turn over ball.
New nerf bars and oem mud flaps.
Transmission was gone through bands adjusted, new updated shift solenoids, pressure transducer, speed sensor.
Transfer case was also gone through.
Just had new exhaust manifold gaskets done. 
Just serviced the drive train and motor, new oil, fuel, and air filter.
New brakes all the way around, all new U joints and carrier bearing in drive line.
The front end is tight and drives straight. 
The interior was professionally detailed you won't find a cleaner one.
The body is straight and nice it does have a few minor dings.
If you are looking for a nice solid truck that needs nothing this it the one!
I'm asking $18.500 you won't find a deal on a truck like this!!
It has a clean title.

body:
QR Code Link to This Post



1997 Ford F-Superduty 1.5 ton dually. Ford didn't make an F-450 in 1997, but this is the next step up from the F-350 and they called it the F-Superduty. 7.5L V8 automatic gas engine with dual gas tanks, regular cab with a rare 11 foot contractor bed (8 full cabinets instead of 6). 153,000 miles. This is a two-owner vehicle, previously government owned, then owned by me. Clean and clear title in hand. The generator pictured in the bed will NOT transfer with the truck. The vise is welded into the bed and WILL transfer with the truck.

I bought it to pull a travel trailer, but I am now upgrading to either a motorhome and don't need the truck anymore, or a fifth wheel and the contractor body doesn't allow for a fifth wheel to hang over the bed, so either way it needs gone.

The good:

-This thing is a monster. Fires right up and runs strong. GCVWR of 25,000lbs.

-Cold A/C and hot heat.

-Am/Fm radio works. (This was a government fleet vehicle, so it's pretty bare bones in terms of options.)

-Includes tow package with brake controller and electric winch connector on the front bumper.

-No cracked glass.

-Good tires.

-All within the last 3,000 miles:

-New brakes, rotors and shoes.
-New power steering pump 
-New Radiator
-New exterior lights
-Oil and transmission fluid changed

The bad:

-The driver's side of the bench seat was torn up when I bought it. I re-stuffed it with foam and covered with duct tape (pictured)

-The emergency overhead lights (amber spinners) don't appear to be connected. I've never tried to turn them on, but I've never even seen a switch with which to turn them on.

-Very minor surface rust on cabinets and overhead rack, with one noticeable dent on the rear bumper (pictured).

-One service panel (very rear, passenger side) is missing the lock, but still opens and closes securely. All other panels have functioning locks.

As I said earlier, I have been using this to pull a travel trailer. I travel full time in my RV and, as a Virginia resident, the vehicle is titled and registered in Virginia. As such, tags will NOT transfer with the truck, Virginia DMV requires surrender of license plates upon sale of a vehicle.

I'm open to trades involving a diesel pickup or motorhome. Please TEXT Jason with any questions at 5seven1.two41.thirty-four44

Includes a full set of mounted Firestone Winterforce snow tires. Only major flaw in the paint is the spot on the left rear above taillight. Have a set of carpet floormats along with the rubber set that is in some pics. Interior is very nice with the only wear being the driver side bolster worn through in the small spot. Been like that for years, hasn't changed. Steering wheel has the light color worn off the leather in places. Back seat under protector cover is perfect, flips up also. Truck has no rust,ever. Also have a full set of OEM fender flares I never put on and the stock OEM grille. Hard to find this nice and well maintained. Runs and drives perfect, no leaks, no smoke, no surprises.  I am listing my 1997 Mazda B2300 pick up truck for sale. I have had this truck since 2011 and have maintained meticulously.  I am the second owner of the truck as I purchased it when it has 60,000 miles on it.  I have religiously changed the oil every 3000 miles and performed all regular maintenance to the truck as needed. Two months ago I just did a timing chain in the truck as well,  so the next owner doesn't have to worry about the timing chain breaking in the future as it is good for another hundred thousand miles! This is the original engine in the truck and it has never been worked on or opened up for any engine problems. There also is a hitch on the truck if you do want to tow a trailer with it.  I have the Firestone Winter force tires on the truck now for the winter time and then I have a separate set of wheels and tires for the spring, summer and fall that I put on. There is minimal if any rust on the truck it is in very good condition. The engine and clutch run and work beautifully.  I don't need to sell the truck just seeing if I would get any interest  or offers on it at this time. I have all of the original documents and papers for the truck and maintenance records on all the work that has been done since I purchased it. Please feel free to email text or give me a call if you have any further questions about the truck, thanks for looking!

Asking $16,000 or best offer.

Car has seen a good combination of city and highway miles.  This car used to belong to my father, who passed away last year.  I am handling the sale of this truck, and my mother, who is head of the estate, is currently the owner of the vehicle and she will be receiving payment from whoever purchases it.

Truck is currently located in Bethlehem.

My father was hard at hearing, so he removed the muffler to hear the engine better.  So the only thing muffling the sound is the catalytic converter.  The sound from the exhaust isn't too loud, though.

Everything on this truck works great.  There are no problems whatsoever, as far as I know.  This truck has been very well maintained, and my father spared no expense in taking care of it.  Everything works, and it drives great.  Four wheel drive works great.  Nonetheless, this truck is used and is being sold AS-IS, with no warranties, guarantees, returns, or refunds of any kind.  Buyer responsible for picking up (or shipping, if need be) of truck.  Deposit of $500 due within 48 hours of auction end.  Cashier check, cash, and PayPal accepted.  Any questions, contact me!

I'm also selling a couch.

body:
QR Code Link to This Post



If you have a problem with this ad, please email me. Thanks

Hi,
I have decided to sell the best truck I have ever owned. It is a 2007 Crew cab 6.6L Duramax diesel longbed. I have driven this thing halfway across the country and it runs excellent with 220k miles! Better gas mileage than my Lexus LX470 too. I was going to keep it but after having the baby we dicided that we have too many personal vehicles that do not get used every day. This thing can pull a house down! It has the LBZ Duramax with 360 hp and 650+ft/lbs of torque. And it has the Allison transmission
It was a fllet vehicle for the power company until it got close to 175k miles, then they sold it. So it has been maintained excellently.

The Chevrolet Silverado 2500HD came in at #2 in a 2016 study by iSeeCars.com ranking the top 10 longest-lasting vehicles. The Silverado 2500HD had 5.7% of vehicles over 200,000 miles, according to the iSeeCars study
The long bed is Rhino lined
5" exhaust, subtle but deep at throttle, like a fire truck
4 door 4dr crewcab
Black leather
Seats 6
2WD
No rattles or shimmy

I do have a leveling lift kit for ir as well as some polished HD wheels/rims andsome 285/75r16 AT tires I can sell as well. I planned to lift it a bit, but we just don't need a truck this big right now, so someone else should have some fun.

Thanks

The vehicle has lots of extras.  Less than 7,000 miles on new BF Goodrich All-Terrain Tires, Roof Rack (Ski accessory rack not included), Tow Package with Tekonsha Trailer Break, Newer Toolbox, New Windshield, Daytime Running Lights, Bedliner, Floor Mats.

This is a one owner, no accident truck with the powerful 5.9 liter Cummins diesel engine and an automatic transmission.  It was traded in by the owner of a mechanical repair shop, and he bought a new Ram. 

This truck has been inspected, and we fixed a few things, and it is ready to go for another two or three hundred thousand miles.  
Other equipment includes an AM/FM CD radio, tilt steering wheel, the ST package, air conditioning, the owner's manual, a tow hitch, a sprayed in black bedliner, a sliding rear window, a black plastic tonneau cover, alloy wheels and 17 inch tires, an auxiliary transmission oil cooler, an anti-spin differential, a 3.73 rear axle, a 34 gallon fuel tank, and more.

 The good- 1/2 ton truck, It is a 4x4 and 4 high, 4 low and 2wd all work, all the power options actually work= power mirrors, power locks, power windows, tilt, cruise, driver seat power and passengers seat power. The trim package is LS- it has a burnt orange exterior and grey cloth interior, am/fm cd player, bench seat with fold down center console, temp gauge/compass on mirror, all interior gauges and exterior lights all seem to work as well. Has a two inch receiver hitch and the tow mode on the dash. Runs great, great glass too... 

 The bad- the light gauge for the trip meter is burnt out, unknown miles (I am sure they are high) but it runs well, the heater core is leaking so right now it is by passed, tires are all poor tread, comes with 4 extra Chevy stock rims, tear in driver's cloth seat, very dirty and needs a detail, passenger side exterior mirror is cracked, body has dents, dings and bed has rust around the wheel fenders.

 This truck would be perfect for a ranch rig, hunting, fishing, camping and not worrying about dents or scratches. If you are after a nice looking truck this is not it. If you are after a cheaper 4wd for work or play then here it is. The pictures make it look nicer than the truck really is. Just being up front. I am asking $2,695 CASH in person (no checks, scams) or I will consider a full or partial trade for Arctic Cat snowmobiles (M6. M7 or M8) or Arctic Cat atv's, some tools/generator with partial cash or a 4 stroke efi dirt bike. The truck is probably worth more parted out but it runs too good to do that. cash talks......

 The Chevy Silverado is located outside Whitehall and can be seen upon appointment. Text me any questions..... 


 KEYWORDS- Arctic Cat, 4x4, jeep, dirt bike, Yamaha, Kawasaki, ktm, Suzuki, Honda, artic cat, M8, tools trade

it's a 2004 chevy colorado. crew cab. 4x4. z71 off-road package. inspected. fully loaded. line-x bed liner with lifetime warranty. 3.5 (5-cylinder) motor & automatic transmission. does have a good amount of miles on the body (242k), however most of it is all highway from work travel. the motor, transmission, transfer, & rear have always been serviced with amsoil. transmission was replaced less than 20k ago. motor just had a full tune-up done this past fall. 31" cooper discoverer atx tires have around 10k on them (i still have the stock z71 wheels & goodyear tires to go with the truck as well). both front & back brakes are brand new. inner & outer tie rods, wheel speed sensors, & power steering rack & pinion (lifetime warranty) were done not too long ago. recently put 4 brand new rancho shocks on it. brand new battery. brand new alternator (lifetime warranty). brand new serpentine belt. temperature positioning sensor. etc.. i know i'm missing a few other things but it's currently in the process of getting some extra minor work done as well that should be done sometime this week or next, would consider selling it as is too. also have aftermarket led headlights, led tailights, led 3rd brake light, & a stainless steel grill insert to go with the truck as well i haven't had the chance to install yet.

long story short this truck was always taken care of & kept in great shape throughout ownership. i'm only the 2nd owner & this truck has never once left me stranded or stuck anywhere & i wouldn't hesitate to take it across country & back. couldn't ask more out of a truck that did more than what i needed it to do & still get anywhere from 20-26 mpg. this is a CASH ONLY, NO TRADES deal. like i said previously i'm not really motivated to sell but if the right offer comes about it's going to be considered. call/text 717-634-four89two if seriously interested.

I "sold" it last fall to a nephew, but when he came to town this spring to pick it up, he didn't like it as much as he had last fall. His loss, I think. It sat in my alley all winter and I turned down several offers for it (because I was going to sell it to my nephew). Yesterday we aired up the tires and put a charger on the battery for about an hour and it started right up. It has two gas tanks, which is really handy and I keep 5 gallons in the back one just in case. It has a trailer hitch, and tie hooks (ask me for the bungee net). The color is more copper than brown - And the price is firm. I'd rather keep it than sell it for less than $500.

body:
QR Code Link to This Post



COPY AND PASTE THE LINK BELOW INTO A NEW BROWSER FOR OVER 80 PICTURES

s1382.photobucket.com/user/dstroeh/library/390143?sort=3&page=1


OVERVIEW

VIN Number 1HTMPAFM37H390XXX

Features/Options:

Air Brakes
Dual Fuel Tanks
Air Ride Drivers Seat
24' Box
102" Box
Translucent Roof
Vented Box
Side Door
2 Rows of E-Track
Maxon 400lb Self Leveling Liftgate 78" X 62"
Air Conditioning
AM/FM Radio
Spring Suspension
25,999 lb GVWR
254" Wheelbase
Maxxforce DT466 220hp Engine

Hello and thank you for taking the time to look at my auction. Please know that I am extremely detail oriented and when I recondition a truck I do it to the level as if I were going to keep it for myself. Needless to say I go much deeper into the detail on these trucks than anyone I have yet to come across. They are mechanically sound, clean as a pin and as close to brand new as I can get them within reason. 

We do not put a truck up for sale with any active codes.

This truck is a PRE-EMISSIONS 2007 International 4300 box truck with 316930 miles. This truck has a DT466 engine (220hp) and is in fantastic condition. No oil leaks and is as mechanically strong as they come. Behind the DT466 is the indestructible 5 speed Automatic Eaton Fuller transmission with overdrive followed by the Spicer rear end. This is one of the most reliable drive trains in the industry. 

This truck came out of a major National fleet with one of the best fleet maintenance records in the industry.

This truck can haul plenty of cargo, especially with the 25,999lb GVWR (NO CDL REQUIRED) and a 24' Truck Body and a Maxon 4400lb 78" X 62" liftgate. I drove this truck over 1100 miles to bring it back to North Carolina with absolutely no issues at all. It has a Whiting roll up door with an opening 91 1/2" wide x 89" tall and 102" wide x 97" tall overall dimension. Truck has an overall clearance of 12' 7". The box comes equipped with a translucent roof, 2 rows of E-Track and a side door.

Inside the cab, you'll find an AM/FM Radio, Air Conditioning, heat, Cruise control, 12v power outlet, an air ride driver's bucket seat and a passenger bench seat with a storage compartment underneath. One of the best features of this truck is the drive train. The Pre-Emissions DT466, the Eaton Fuller automatic transmission and the Spicer rear end are a bulletproof drive train combination. This combo has a proven track record over the years and is extremely reliable. Time has proven that if properly maintained it can go for 1 million miles without a rebuild. Another fantastic features of the DT466 is it's ability to be "in Frame Rebuilt" saving thousands if a rebuild is needed. It is becoming more and more difficult to find these Pre-emissions trucks with an automatic transmission. If you're searching for a great work truck in like new condition, you found it.

CONDITION REPORT
This truck is exceptionally clean. The entire frame from the cab back as well as the front suspension, have been sandblasted down to the bare metal primed and painted (3 coats). The handles, steps, differential, springs and mirrors have all been freshly painted. The engine has been steam cleaned and there are no oil leaks. The wheels, hubs and lug nuts have also been sandblasted and repainted. Inside I took the seats out cleaned and repainted the frames. The entire interior was steam cleaned including the back panel and headliner. All of the panels and dash shine and are not dull. The entire exterior of the box and cab (including the door jams) have been professionally repainted and looks fantastic. The interior of the box was steam cleaned as well as the oak floor. This truck is immaculate, clean as a pin. You can not appreciate it until you see it in person the pictures just don't do it justice. 

It is easy to tell that it has not been abused or overworked and obviously cared for properly. We send all of our trucks to the local dealer and have a health check run on them. They are gone through top to bottom and front to back. We spend an average of $3000 on the mechanical aspects alone when putting our trucks through the refurbishing process. We make all the necessary repairs to fix any and all issues that were identified. Cosmetically on this truck we replaced the headlights, gear shift cover, Dock Bumpers, and DOT Reflective Tape just to name afew items. There are absolutely no mechanical issues with this truck. It is a good solid runner ready to go to work. No squeaks/rattles at idle or cruising down the road. It is as quiet of a truck at as you will ever find. 

All of the interior features are functioning normally and there are no mechanical or drivability issues. It is sitting on 22.5" tires. The tire treads measure: front Left 10/32, Left rear outside 13/32, inside 13/32. Right front 11.5/32, right rear outside 12.7/32, inside 12.7/32. Please don't hesitate to email me with any questions you have and I will respond as soon as possible. I encourage communication and will gladly respond to all questions with as much information as I possibly can.
You will be hard pressed to find a truck in this condition for this price.

Been like that for years, hasn't changed. Steering wheal has the light color worn off the leather in places. Back seat under protector cover is perfect, flips up also. Truck has no rust,ever. Also have a full set of OEM fender flares I never put on and the stock OEM grille. Hard to find this nice and well maintained. Runs and drives perfect, no leaks, no smoke, no surprises. Power heated leather seats and power mirrors. Sliding rear glass. Haven't been sitting in the truck since August (bush teacher) but if I recall, it is the Limited Package. No body damage, paint is good, and the interior is excellent. No rips in seats, not even the driver's seat. I purchased this truck with 2015 PFD while living on POW Island in SE Alaska. Put new tires on the vehicle then and have only driven it about 5,000 miles since I purchased it. This is a great truck. I have wavered back and forth about selling it. I am moving to Dillingham over the summer and will be purchasing another vehicle this summer while in KC, MO and I am trying to avoid the temptation to pay the barge fee for two vehicle. So, if I can get a fair price for the truck, I plan on just shipping the vehicle I return from Missouri with.

If you are interested, please text me and I will text back or call if you wish. I don't mind you giving me a call, but since I am a teacher I would rather not have my phone ring during class. If I take a call, they think they should be able to do the same.

Hard to find, excellent condition, 2006 Sundowner 737 two-horse, bumper pull aluminum 

trailer with tack room. Tires have less than 200 miles on them. Bearings packed and brakes serviced less than 25 miles ago by Sundowner dealer. Clear 

title. Extra tall and Extra wide so fits most horses. No leaks. Super friendly - horses feel safe and load easily into this trailer. Easy and safe walk 

through into tack room while loading the horses! Loading ramp. Hay mangers. Drop down windows with safety bars. Fully ventilated. Water tank in tack 

room. Two saddle racks in tack room, as well as hanging racks for tack hooks or to hang show clothes. This trailer is friendly and easy to pull, turn, 

and back up if you are just starting out towing. Best trailer I have ever owned and I would never sell it until now - getting out of horses! Massey 

Ferguson 283 Tractor and loader 80hp, 2wd, dual remotes, wheel weights, comes with bucket and hay spear, New tires on the front, runs great, fully 

serviced and ready to go. Delivery Available *Motivated Seller* Tractor is located in Hardin Tx. $8,750 Call Only 4zero92012026. Handmade to exact 

scientific specifications to draw the most bats possible to your yard/farm. Holds approximately 100 bats. Completely made of cedar, waterproof, rust free 

screws and climbing netting installed on the interior to aid the bats in nesting. Low cost to comparable items online. Instructions and suggestions on 

hanging included. Why would you want bats to visit in the evening???? Bats eat 1200 mosquitoes an hour, with each averaging about 8000 a night! Make your 

yard safer and more pleasant to be in, and help the environment, too. 22" tall x 17" wide x 4" deep Pull Start 8hp. Runs well. You can put a battery on 

it and it will start with starter. Starts easily with one pull. Very strong. Pokey is a 21-22 year old kid broke sorrel gelding. Saddle him up and ride. 

Easy keeper, friendly and in good shape. This horse has many years of riding left. He is flat footed on front so if you plan to ride on hard surfaces he 

will need shoes or boots. You may have your choice of a 14" or 18" saddle. Deals includes saddle, pad, breast collar, and halter or I will take $1000 for 

the horse. Local pickup only and cash! I have January kids from a Fat Albert (Milligan) X Swagger (Sayer) available.Will make great fall show kids. Some 

small frame will go to early spring shows Casey and Doug are selling Seasoned Oak firewood all year for you guys and gals that are Pit Smoking or for 

your Outdoor Kitchen. Also, if you're going camping you got to have wood for that great camping experience. This past winter we have sold over 25 full 

cords and everyone says how clean and seasoned the wood is and that's because we store all the wood we split indoors so that it is not in the rain or not 

covered like most guys selling wood. If the wood you buy is dark it's been out in the weather. This is our fifth year selling cords of oak and have 

returning customers every year. if you need seasoned oak, call my wife at 936-3five5-7one28 Casey and Doug are selling Seasoned Oak firewood all year for
