months old. They are a rare breed that has great personality are very inquisitive and they are great forgers ...excellent for free ranging. $50 for the 

set. I don't really know much about this other than we got it from my wife's grandmother 10+ years ago. It has ornate hand carved handles and drawer 

faces and dovetail joints on the drawers. There are 3 carved drawers and the very bottom "baseboard" pulls out as a drawer as well. The mirror is really 

beautiful, too - we had it mounted in the entryway of our 1912-era house for years and it fit right in! We have moved to a new house and this no longer 

matches our style, so I hope someone else can enjoy it like we have.We are in our 13th season Wadena fleamarket has indoor and outdoor spaces available 

call Susan 12six or Corey 218 640 117one we also have free camping for our venders .Pair of Mid Century Modern (1950s) Pink Flamingo Ceramic Figurines. 

Unmarked, but looks like those manufactured by Maddux of California. Excellent Condition with vibrant colors and smooth, shiny finish! No flaws, cracks, 

chips, or crazing. From my parents' estate. Smoke-free, no odors. $25 for both flamingos. Perfect for Mid Century Modern decorators or Flamingo 

collectors! Rare to find the pair as one is usually lost or broken.I've picked up several pieces of beautiful vintage glassware from estate sales and 

antique shops over the years, but now I am downsizing my life and looking forward to providing part of this collection to a glass enthusiast for a great 

price. The 3 boots, the top hat and the candy dish are all Fenton. The stem vases are vintage but from unknown makers and the two depression era glass 

pieces were acquired at an estate sale at an old St. Paul mansion on Summit Ave several years ago. I am selling these pieces as a lot only and do not 

want to part it out. The price asked is a great deal for the buyer, so I don't expect these to last long... Look forward to your inquiries!1920's china 

features an Eastern Rosella Parrot in the middle while Hummingbirds , Birds of Paradise, and Butterflies along the edges amid colorful flowers. China is 

edged in gold , 8 dinner plates, 9 luncheon, 8 salad, 11 fruit bowls, 4 cups and 8 saucers, birds, all in mint condition, no chips.Vintage solid brass 

envelope knife / paper knife / letter opener in perfect vintage condition with Ship Victory as the handle. High quality brass. It has stamped engraving -

months old. They are a rare breed that has great personality are very inquisitive and they are great forgers ...excellent for free ranging. $50 for the 

set. I don't really know much about this other than we got it from my wife's grandmother 10+ years ago. It has ornate hand carved handles and drawer 

faces and dovetail joints on the drawers. There are 3 carved drawers and the very bottom "baseboard" pulls out as a drawer as well. The mirror is really 

beautiful, too - we had it mounted in the entryway of our 1912-era house for years and it fit right in! We have moved to a new house and this no longer 

matches our style, so I hope someone else can enjoy it like we have.We are in our 13th season Wadena fleamarket has indoor and outdoor spaces available 

call Susan 12six or Corey 218 640 117one we also have free camping for our venders .Pair of Mid Century Modern (1950s) Pink Flamingo Ceramic Figurines.

chips, or crazing. From my parents' estate. Smoke-free, no odors. $25 for both flamingos. Perfect for Mid Century Modern decorators or Flamingo 

collectors! Rare to find the pair as one is usually lost or broken.I've picked up several pieces of beautiful vintage glassware from estate sales and 

antique shops over the years, but now I am downsizing my life and looking forward to providing part of this collection to a glass enthusiast for a great 

price. The 3 boots, the top hat and the candy dish are all Fenton. The stem vases are vintage but from unknown makers and the two depression era glass

body:
QR Code Link to This Post


Mark IV 7.4L/454, TH400, 14 bolt rear end with G80

This is my daily driver. It has about 202,000 miles on the body, the motor was rebuilt at some point in its life and i had the transmission rebuilt and a shift kit installed about 30,000 miles ago. I only run Premium gas (93 octane) in this truck. Regular oil changes every 3,000 miles. It does have a rear main seal leak. The tires have been rotated and road force balanced since new, every 6000 miles, and still have good, even tread. The exterior is in decent shape. The paint is peeling on the hood a bit but it looks really nice when its washed and waxed. The interior is in nice shape. I repainted all the interior plastic pieces with SEM ColorCoat paint. It is wired for an amp and subwoofer. Its not shown in the pictures but i have spare tire tool kit and case for behind the seats. I do have an unpainted fiberglass roll pan and smooth wiper cowl to go with the truck, if wanted. This is a great running truck, i HATE to sell it but i would like something a little newer and with more space. Two bucket seats in a single cab truck doesnt work well with a wife and baby.

In the past 3 years ive done/replaced:

- Radiator
- Alternator
- Moog Upper control arm assemblies
- Belltech front and rear shocks
- Front wheel bearings
- Hub Assemblies
- Brake pads
- ACDelco Proportioning Valve
- Knock Sensor

- Dana Spicer U Joints

- Windshield

- March Performance Underdrive Pulleys
- ACDelco double platinum spark plugs
- ACDelco spark plug wires
- MSD distributor cap
- Heater Core
- Water pump
- Fan Clutch
